-- Falklands May Get $176 Billion Oil Tax Windfall, Telegraph Says
-- B y   K i t   C h e l l e l
-- 2012-02-12T09:54:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/falklands-may-get-176-billion-oil-tax-windfall-telegraph-says.html
The Falkland Islands could benefit
from $176 billion in taxes from prospective oil and natural gas
fields, according to a report by Edison Investment Research
cited by the  Sunday Telegraph .  The report said the windfall would transform the islands,
which currently have tax revenues of about $40 million from
fishing and other industries, according to the Telegraph.  To contact the reporter on this story:
